obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35541)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35541&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Taxation Laws (Continuation and Validation of`
  line `Recovery Proceedings) Act, 1964.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35542)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35542&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "assessee", in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) the Excess Profits Tax Act, 1940 (15 of 1940), or the Business Profits Tax Act, 1947 (21`
  line `of 1947), means a person by whom the tax or any other sum is payable under that Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Estate Duty Act, 1953 (34 of 1953), means a person accountable or an accountable`
  line `person as defined in that Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) any other scheduled Act, means an assessee as defined in that Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Government dues", in relation to any scheduled Act, means any tax, duty, penalty, fine,`
  line `interest, annuity deposit or any other sum payable to the Government by an assessee under that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "scheduled Act" means an Act specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) "Taxing Authority", in relation to any scheduled Act, means an officer (by whatever name`
  line `called) empowered to serve upon an assessee a notice of demand in respect of any Government dues`
  line `under that Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Tax Recovery Officer", in relation to any scheduled Act, means a Tax Recovery Officer as`
  line `defined in that Act and where there is no such definition, means an officer (by whatever name called)`
  line `to whom a certificate for the recovery of arrears of Government dues may be issued under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35543)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Continuation and validation of certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35543&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any notice of demand in`
  line `respect of any Government dues is served upon an assessee by a Taxing Authority under any scheduled`
  line `Act, and any appeal or other proceeding is filed or taken in respect of such Government dues, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) where such Government dues are enhanced in such appeal or proceeding, the Taxing`
  line `Authority shall serve upon the assessee another notice of demand only in respect of the amount by`
  line `which such Government dues are enhanced and any proceedings in relation to such Government dues`
  line `as are covered by the notice or notices of demand served upon him before the disposal of such appeal`
  line `or proceeding may, without the service of any fresh notice of demand, be continued from the stage at`
  line `which such proceedings stood immediately before such disposal;`
  line
  line `(b) where such Government dues are reduced in such appeal or proceeding,--`
  line
  line `(i) it shall not be necessary for the Taxing Authority to serve upon the assessee a fresh notice`
  line `of demand;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Taxing Authority shall give intimation of the fact of such reduction to the assessee,`
  line `and where a certificate has been issued to the Tax Recovery Officer for the recovery of such`
  line `amount, also to that officer;`
  line
  line `(iii) any proceedings initiated on the basis of the notice or notices of demand served upon the`
  line `assessee before the disposal of such appeal or proceeding may be continued in relation to the`
  line `amount so reduced from the stage at which such proceedings stood immediately before such`
  line disposal;
  line
  line `(c) no proceedings in relation to such Government dues (including the imposition of penalty or`
  line `charging of interest) shall be invalid by reason only that no fresh notice of demand was served upon`
  line `the assessee after the disposal of such appeal or proceeding or that such Government dues have been`
  line `enhanced or reduced in such appeal or proceeding:`
  line
  line `Provided that if as a result of any final order such Government dues (other than annuity deposit)`
  line `have been reduced and the penalty imposed on the assessee for default in payment thereof exceeds the`
  line `amount so reduced, the excess shall not be recovered, and if it has already been recovered, it shall be`
  line `refunded to the assessee on an application made by him to the Taxing Authority wihin such time and`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the amount of penalty imposed on the assessee for failure to make any`
  line `annuity deposit exceeds one-half of the amount of the annuity deposit required to be made as a result`
  line `of such order, the excess shall not be recovered and if it has already been recovered, shall be refunded`
  line `to the assessee on an application made by him to the Taxing Authority within such time and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any Government dues are reduced in such appeal or proceeding and`
  line `the assessee is entitled to any refund thereof, such refund shall be made in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of that Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that no fresh notice of demand shall be necessary`
  line `in any case where the amount of Government dues is not varied as a result of any order passed in any`
  line `appeal or other proceeding under any scheduled Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of`
  line `any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35544)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to amend the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35544&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, add the name of any Central Act providing for the imposition or levy of any tax or duty in the`
  line `Schedule and on the issue of any such notification, the Act so added shall be deemed to be an Act`
  line `specified in the Schedule within the meaning of clause (c) of section 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35545)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Act to have retrospective effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35545&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall apply and shall be deemed`
  line `always to have applied, in relation to every notice of demand served upon an assessee by any Taxing`
  line `Authority under any scheduled Act whether such notice was or is served before or after the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35546)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35546&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line difficulty.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35547)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392&sectionId=35547&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00021_196411_1517807322392
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may ^1[by notification in the Official Gazette]`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or ^2[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, that rule shall thereafter have effect, only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or annulment`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
